FR940826-2-00151 FR940826-2-00079 Self-Regulatory Organizations; Applications for Unlisted Trading Privileges; Notice and Opportunity for Hearing; Philadelphia Stock Exchange, Incorporated August 22, 1994. The above name national securities exchange has filed applications with the Securities and Exchange Commission (``Commission'') pursuant to Section 12(f)(1)(B) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and Rule 12f&hyph;1 thereunder for unlisted trading privileges in the following securities: Chilgener S.A. American Depository Shares, Representing 4 Shares of Common Stock (File No. 7&hyph;12851) Shandong Huaneng Power Development Co. Ltd. Common Stock, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12852) TVX Gold, Inc. Common Shares, No Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12853) Amax Gold, Inc. Series B Conv. Pfd. Stock, $1.00 Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12854) Citicorp Dep. Shares each representing 1.10th of a share Adj. Rate Cum. Pfd. Stock, No Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12855) United States Surgical Corporation $2.20 Dep. Shares (Each Representing 1/50th of a share of Series A Conv. Pfd. Stock) (Dividend Enhanced Conv. Stock-DECS) (File No. 7&hyph;12856) Superior Surgical Manufacturing Co. Common Shares, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12857) Trigen Energy Corporation Common Shares, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12858) Consolidated Papers, Inc. Common Stock Shares, $1.00 Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12859) Ford Holdings, Inc. Depository Shares Each Representing 1.400 of a share of Cum. Pfd Stock (File No. 7&hyph;12860) Commonwealth Edison Company $2.425 Cum. Pfd Stock (File No. 7&hyph;12861) John Hancock Bank and Thrift Opportunity Fund Common Shares of Beneficial Interest, No Par Value (File No. 7&hyph;12862) These securities are listed and registered on one or more other national securities exchanges and are reported in the consolidated transaction reporting system. Interested persons are invited to submit on or before September 13, 1994, written data, views and arguments concerning the above-referenced application. Persons desiring to make written comments should file three copies thereof with the Secretary of the Securities and Exchange Commission, 450 5th Street, NW., Washington, DC 20549. Following this opportunity for hearing, the Commission will approve the application if it finds, based upon all the information available to it, that the extensions of unlisted trading privileges pursuant to such applications are consistent with the maintenance of fair and orderly markets and the protection of investors. For the Commission, by the Division of Market Regulation, pursuant to delegated authority. Jonathan G. Katz, Secretary. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;21065 Filed 8&hyph;25&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 8010&hyph;01&hyph;M
